reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are so stinking cute
reviews.reviewText: I got the Flesh Pink. These are so stinking cute, I love them. Size is accurate. They can be used for so many things. The plastic is thick, the trim is cute and sturdy. Zipper worked great and seemed to be good quailty. I hope they have or will have larger sizes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really good price for 3 bags!
reviews.reviewText: I looked for travel and makeup bags on Amazon and these were the best price, and clear with purple fabric-my favorite color!I use one regularly and it fits all my makeup. I recently traveled, and it fit 6 two ounce bottles, a tooth brush and denture brush, mini toothpaste tube, mini mouthwash bottle, denture tablets, denture adhesive tube and two ounce spray bottle, with room to spare!That leaves me with the one extra bag, just in case! Sturdy, roomy bags at great price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Liquid Travel Kit
reviews.reviewText: This was perfect for traveling internationally or domestically with carry on bags only. The three pack was perfect for my family. Exactly as described and works perfectly. Wish we could not have so much plastic in the world but this was designed for traveling easily and quickly. I would definitely recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good Size, But Cheap Plastic
reviews.reviewText: These work great for me since I don’t travel often. I’m not sure how well they would hold up to frequent use though. The plastic is thick enough, but still feels a bit cheap and the zipper seems pretty flimsy. I still think they’re worth the cost though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely love these bags. It took the guess work out of how much to pack. And it’s in a nice make up type bag that I can include so much more than just my liquids. I’ve actually gotten used to just using it as my make up bag all of the time. I love the size, the quality and the value. I personally think these are perfect.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect TSA toiletry cases
reviews.reviewText: Perfect size, holds more than others I've had, sturdy, thick and well made. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for traveling with children
reviews.reviewText: I love these little travel bags. When we travel with our son there are so many extra products we need to bring along (children's toothpaste, children's sunscreen, special lotion and bath soap for sensitive skin). These bags help to keep everything super organized in the suitcase. They are also very fairly priced. Would highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great travel bags
reviews.reviewText: Very pleased with this product. I purchased it as a toiletries travel bag, irrespective of its TSA qualifications. Just tried it out on a 10-day vacation, and it performed superbly. It’s amazing how many items will fit into the bag. Its very sturdy see-through plastic shell and heavy-weight zipper gives me confidence that it will hold up in the long term. The fact that I got three bags from this seller for the same price that other suppliers were selling two bags was a nice bonus too.
Worked perfectly, good size , easy to see what's inside. Would buy again.
Product as stated, have used similar, but these better quality. Will be great for predicted use

reviews.reviewTitle: TSA Approved But Not 1L CATSC (Canadian) Approved
reviews.reviewText: Love these bags as they’re sturdy and see through, making screening simpler. HOWEVER, both my mother, sister, and I have been pulled over on separate trips in different airports by Canaidan airport security and required to relinquish items in order to fit into shapeless 1L ziploc bags that CATSC provides. Sucks to leave behind expensive cosmetic items, but overall a sturdy bag. Can’t find anywhere in the ad what the volume of the bag is but likely larger than the 1L allowed.
